# Hi, I'm Ezechiel Sawadogo

Master’s student in Language and Computer Science at Sorbonne University.

My academic work focuses on the intersection of language, computation, and interpretation, with a particular interest in:

- Natural Language Processing
- OCR and document analysis
- Machine learning
- Digital humanities
- Language, literature, and power

## Selected Projects

- [ocr-corpus-analysis](https://github.com/sawadogoezechiel09-alt/ocr-corpus-analysis)  
  OCR evaluation and corpus analysis project developed for NLP coursework at Sorbonne University.

- [byzantine-seal-recognition](https://github.com/sawadogoezechiel09-alt/byzantine-seal-recognition)  
  Deep learning project on Greek character recognition from Byzantine seals.

- [earthquake-research-presentation](https://github.com/sawadogoezechiel09-alt/earthquake-research-presentation)  
  Research project combining exploratory analysis and multimodal methods for natural disaster classification.

- [car-price-prediction](https://github.com/sawadogoezechiel09-alt/car-price-prediction)  
  Machine learning and statistical analysis project for car price prediction using vehicle specifications.

- [insta-manager](https://github.com/sawadogoezechiel09-alt/insta-manager)  
  Python-based content planning tool with scheduling, hashtag generation, CTA suggestions, and CSV export.

## Current Direction

I am especially interested in projects that connect computational methods with texts, discourse, visual documents, and cultural analysis.

## Profile

This GitHub gathers coursework, research-oriented experiments, and applied projects in NLP, OCR, machine learning, and data analysis.
